{"type":"message","id":"abcc8028","parentId":"cfc27a7a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:48:42.383Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yuspra8xqfbr_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4626\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1' new_len=1821\n[mutation proposed] research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\n[master db17291] pulse: 2026-03-24 124817\n 6 files changed, 289 insertions(+), 78 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 124817.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 124817.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 124316.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 124817 - The CFI Compression Synthesis has identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" and derived a concrete three-dimensional filter formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). The next logical step is to implement Strategy C (hybrid scoring) and compare it against the freq-only and CFI-hard baselines already tested.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"young-bloom","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4626\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1' new_len=1821\n[mutation proposed] research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\n[master db17291] pulse: 2026-03-24 124817\n 6 files changed, 289 insertions(+), 78 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 124817.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 124817.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 124316.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 124817 - The CFI Compression Synthesis has identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" and derived a concrete three-dimensional filter formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). The next logical step is to implement Strategy C (hybrid scoring) and compare it against the freq-only and CFI-hard baselines already tested.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370922379}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f438f01","parentId":"abcc8028","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:48:42.387Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yuspra8xqfbr_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 124316\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT_DESIGN.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment is pending\r\n2. I have the CFI analysis results showing that:\r\n   - 44.8% have CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n   - Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n   - Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to design and implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Creating a baseline using frequency-based compression\r\n2. Creating an improved version using CFI weights\r\n3. Comparing next-pulse prediction accuracy between the two\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files I have to work with. I should check the state directory and research directory structure to understand what's available.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take is to create an experiment design document that outlines how to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment, and potentially start implementing the comparison logic.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what specific file edit would advance the goals most directly...\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at what's in the research directory (especially CFI_RESULTS.md and any compression-related work)\r\n2. Design the experiment\r\n3. Potentially create a script or document for the CFI-weighted compression comparison\r\n\r\nThe most actionable item is to design and document the CFI-weighted compression experiment so it can be run in the next pulse. This would involve creating a new document that:\r\n- Defines the experimental setup\r\n- Specifies the baseline (frequency-only compression)\r\n- Specifies the CFI-weighted approach\r\n- Defines success metrics\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment design document.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of invariants have low causal fidelity (CFI<0.7), meaning frequency-based compression is mostly capturing metaprogramming artifacts rather than true causal structure. The next step is to implement and compare CFI-weighted compression against the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment design document for the CFI-weighted compression comparison, specifying the methodology, baseline, and success metrics.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** Ready for execution\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression for predicting the next meaningful pulse, because it filters metaprogramming artifacts (CFI≈0) and preserves true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experimental Setup\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n- Weight invariants by raw frequency\r\n- Compress invariant set to top-K by frequency\r\n- Use resulting compressed state to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n- Weight invariants by CFI score\r\n- Apply hard filter: exclude CFI<0.3 (noise/metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Compress invariant set to top-K by CFI-weighted frequency\r\n- Use resulting compressed state to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\n## Metrics\r\n1. **Prediction accuracy**: % of predicted invariant anchors that appear in actual next pulse\r\n2. **Noise reduction**: % of metaprogramming artifacts removed by CFI filter\r\n3. **Causal signal preservation**: % of high-CFI invariants retained\r\n4. **Compression ratio**: final invariant count vs original\r\n\r\n## Execution\r\n```bash\r\n# Analyze invariants from recent pulses\r\n./pulse.ps1 --analyze-cfi-compression\r\n\r\n# Run comparison experiment\r\n./pulse.ps1 --experiment=cfi-compression\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- CFI filter removes ~45% of invariants (CFI≈0 noise)\r\n- CFI-weighted compression should improve prediction accuracy by preserving causal structure\r\n- This validates Breakaway's bet: causal fidelity > frequency for long-term convergence\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:43:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370922383}}
