{"type":"message","id":"e9032714","parentId":"9e4b871f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:48:49.415Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z6a39uii4ej9_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 124817\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on one concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE - sandbox foundation\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE - architecture cross-analysis + integration spec\r\n\r\nKey insight: The CFI Compression Experiment revealed that CFI≥0.7 AND freq<60 is too aggressive. They discovered the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens like \"for next instantiation\" with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\nThey've identified a three-dimensional filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n\r\nAnd a concrete scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe next pending experiment is: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThis is a logical next step - they have the formula, now they need to test it.\r\n\r\nLooking at the files created:\r\n- research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\n- research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n- research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n\r\nThey mention running an experiment comparing freq-only vs CFI-hard on 200 pulses. The next step would be to implement Strategy C (the hybrid scoring) and run that experiment.\r\n\r\nThe concrete action should be: Create a new experiment script that implements the hybrid scoring formula and tests it against the previous approaches.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what would be most impactful:\r\n1. Create a new experiment comparing the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Update the synthesis doc with the new three-dimensional filter\r\n3. Start implementing the scoring function\r\n\r\nGiven the \"Constant Format Problem\" insight, the most logical next action is to create a new experiment script that implements Strategy C - the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring approach.\r\n\r\nLet me write this as a PowerShell script that:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll craft a precise scoring mechanism that filters tokens using a multi-dimensional approach. The script will calculate a hybrid score by combining CFI (Contextual Frequency Importance) with frequency-based normalization, targeting tokens in the 0.5-0.95 CFI range and frequency between 3-120. This targeted filtering will help isolate meaningful tokens while excluding metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis has identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" and derived a concrete three-dimensional filter formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). The next logical step is to implement Strategy C (hybrid scoring) and compare it against the freq-only and CFI-hard baselines already tested.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` implementing Strategy C using the three-dimensional filter and hybrid scoring formula to compare against prior results.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C\r\n# Comparing: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring vs Freq-only vs CFI-hard\r\n# Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n\r\n$script:pulseDir = \"$script:root/pulses\"\r\n$script:outputDir = \"$script:root/research/hybrid_results\"\r\n$script:stats = @{\r\n    hybrid = @{correct=0; total=0}\r\n    freq_only = @{correct=0; total=0}\r\n    cfi_hard = @{correct=0; total=0}\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-HybridScore {\r\n    param($token, $cfi, $freq)\r\n    $normalizedFreq = [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120.0)\r\n    return $cfi * $normalizedFreq\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Test-Strategies {\r\n    param($tokens)\r\n    foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n        # Strategy C: Hybrid (new)\r\n        $hybrid = Get-HybridScore $t.token $t.cfi $t.freq\r\n        if ($hybrid -ge 0.25) {\r\n            $script:stats.hybrid.total++\r\n            if ($t.isResearch) { $script:stats.hybrid.correct++ }\r\n        }\r\n        # Freq-only: threshold=60\r\n        if ($t.freq -ge 60) {\r\n            $script:stats.freq_only.total++\r\n            if ($t.isResearch) { $script:stats.freq_only.correct++ }\r\n        }\r\n        # CFI-hard: threshold=0.7\r\n        if ($t.cfi -ge 0.7) {\r\n            $script:stats.cfi_hard.total++\r\n            if ($t.isResearch) { $script:stats.cfi_hard.correct++ }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Export-Results {\r\n    $results = @()\r\n    foreach ($strategy in @(\"hybrid\",\"freq_only\",\"cfi_hard\")) {\r\n        $s = $script:stats[$strategy]\r\n        $prec = if ($s.total -gt 0) { $s.correct / $s.total } else { 0 }\r\n        $results += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            Strategy = $strategy\r\n            Precision = [Math]::Round($prec, 4)\r\n            TotalSelected = $s.total\r\n            Correct = $s.correct\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    $results | Format-Table -AutoSize\r\n    $results | ConvertTo-Json | Out-File \"$outputDir/strategy_comparison.json\"\r\n}\r\nfile: research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:48:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370929413}}
